A top student, Juliet Akinyi from Kiandutu slum in Thika has been awarded a scholarship to study Pharmacy at a local university by Bidco Africa. Her sister Beryl Auma also received a scholarship for secondary school. Their mother Joyce Achieng was offered a job. CEO Vimal Shah on Friday said he saw the family&rsquo;s story on a local TV station and offered to help. Akinyi scored an A in last year&rsquo;s KCSE exam.